The '''Alexandria Center of Arts''' ({{lang-ar|مركز الاسكندرية للابداع}}, ''Alexandria Center for Creativity'') is an [[arts center]], community [[exhibition hall|exhibitions space]] and [[cultural center]] in the city of [[Alexandria]], [[Egypt]], overseen by the [[Ministry of Culture (Egypt)|Egyptian Ministry of Culture]]. The center was officially opened on 29 October 2001, by [[Farouk Hosni]], Minister of Culture, and then-President [[Hosni Mubarak]]'s wife, [[Suzanne Mubarak]].

